• Cash on Hand (End amount): 5,603,438.00
• Bank Deposits (End amount): 3,642,142.45
• Total Current Liabilities (End amount): 2,110,671.05

Step 2: Sum the available cash assets.
  Total Cash = Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits
  Total Cash = 5,603,438.00 + 3,642,142.45 = 9,245,580.45

Step 3: Compute the Cash to Current Debt Ratio.
  Ratio = Total Cash / Total Current Liabilities
  Ratio = 9,245,580.45 / 2,110,671.05 ≈ 4.38

Thus, the Cash to Current Debt Ratio is approximately 4.38.
